  <title>Gio.FILE_ATTRIBUTE_STANDARD_SORT_ORDER</title>
  <p>A key in the "standard" namespace for setting the sort order of a file.
Corresponding <link xref="Gio.FileAttributeType"/> is <link xref="Gio.FileAttributeType"/>.int32.
An example use would be in file managers, which would use this key
to set the order files are displayed. Files with smaller sort order
should be sorted first, and files without sort order as if sort order
was zero.</p>

